# Scroll Stage — Cursor rules

This project uses the Scroll Stage architecture: one sticky pin per scroll-section, multiple stacked videos and captions that crossfade as the user scrolls. Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, no framework, no build step.

## Stack

- Vanilla HTML, CSS, JS. No React, no Vue, no bundler.
- Lenis smooth scroll via CDN: `https://unpkg.com/lenis@1.1.14/dist/lenis.min.js`
- Google Fonts via `<link>` in `<head>`
- Static hosting (GitHub Pages, Vercel, Netlify)

## File structure

```
index.html
styles.css
app.js
media/         # mp4's, all-keyframe encoded
docs/          # optional: SPEC.md, PROMPT.md as reference
```

Stick to this layout. No subfolders for components.

## Naming conventions (BEM-ish)

```
.stage              outer scroll section
.stage__track       scroll track (height = N × 100vh)
.stage__pin         sticky pinned container (100dvh)
.stage__media       stacked videos
.stage__video       individual video (use is-active modifier)
.stage__captions    stacked captions
.stage__caption     individual caption
.stage__caption--hero    full-width hero variant
.stage__caption--left    text in left column
.stage__caption--right   text in right column
.stage__caption--full    full-width content (e.g. product grid)
.stage__scrim       gradient overlay (--left, --right, --hero variants)

.chapter__card      text container inside stage__caption
.chapter__kicker    eyebrow (mono, small caps)
.chapter__num       big display number
.chapter__title     italic chapter title
.chapter__body      body paragraph
```

When adding new captions, use the same naming. Do not invent new class trees.

## Required CSS patterns

```css
html { scrollbar-gutter: stable; }      /* prevents horizontal page shift */

.stage__track { height: calc(var(--ch-count, 1) * 100vh); }
.stage__pin   { position: sticky; top: 0; height: 100dvh; overflow: hidden; isolation: isolate; }
.stage__video { position: absolute; inset: 0; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.55s; }
.stage__video.is-active { opacity: 1; }

.stage__caption {
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  display: grid; align-items: center; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  /* content shell on big screens, shell-pad on narrow */
  padding: 0 max(var(--shell-pad), calc((100% - var(--shell-max)) / 2));
  opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.6s; pointer-events: none;
}
.stage__caption.is-active { opacity: 1; pointer-events: auto; }
```

Use `100dvh` not `100vh` for pinned containers (iOS Safari address bar issue).

## Required JS patterns

- One central `requestAnimationFrame` loop. All scroll-driven updates subscribe via a shared `subscribers` Set.
- Lazy blob preload: only the first video loads on init. Adjacent videos load when the chapter becomes active. Never preload all videos upfront.
- Scrub state per-chapter with snap-on-activate to prevent backward lerp on re-entry.
- Velocity cap: `maxStep = dt` so the video plays at most 1× real-time regardless of scroll speed.
- Anchor handler: `<a href="#caption-id">` links must compute scroll position based on caption index in stage track (not `offsetTop`, which is 0 inside a sticky pin).

See app.js for reference implementation. Do not regress these behaviors.

## Design tokens

Always use CSS custom properties for colors, fonts, spacing. Defined in `:root`:

```css
--paper, --ink, --ember, --ember-soft   colors
--f-display, --f-body, --f-mono         fonts
--ease, --ease-spring, --ease-snap      easings
--shell-max: 1360px                     content width cap
--shell-pad: clamp(20px, 4vw, 56px)     side gutter
```

Never hardcode hex values, never hardcode pixel spacing. Always go through tokens.

## Copy and content rules

- **No em-dashes** (—). Use comma, period, colon.
- **No fake history** (e.g. "since 1932" if untrue). Be honest about what the site is.
- **Specific over abstract.** "Twelve minutes kneading" beats "lots of care".
- **Short sentences.** Max 3 sentences per chapter body.
- **Numbers do work.** Each chapter benefits from one specific number.
- **First line upright, second line italic in accent.** Display headings follow this rhythm.

## What not to do

- Don't add scroll listeners directly. Use the rAF loop's `subscribers`.
- Don't preload all videos at init.
- Don't use Inter font.
- Don't use pure black `#000`. Use off-black (`var(--ink)`).
- Don't wrap content in extra divs unless it earns its keep.
- Don't add a `package.json`, build tool, or framework.
- Don't add tracking scripts or third-party widgets without asking.
- Don't change the stage class structure.

## Video encoding

All chapter videos must be encoded with all-keyframes for smooth scrubbing:

```bash
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf "scale=960:-2" -c:v libx264 -preset slow -crf 24 \
  -g 1 -keyint_min 1 -sc_threshold 0 -an -movflags +faststart output.mp4
```

Target size: 3-6 MB per 8-second clip. Total media folder under 50 MB.

## Performance budget

- Initial JS: under 30 KB (Lenis ~10 KB + app.js ~10 KB)
- Initial video: 1 (active video only, lazy-loaded as blob)
- 60 fps during scroll on M1 MacBook
- Zero horizontal layout shift (scrollbar gutter stable)

## When in doubt

Read `docs/SPEC.md` (if present) for the full reference. Match its patterns exactly.
